From 40e6ad1c50d327d3a3dae656406f327cbf81097c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Juan Manuel Lopez Carrillo <juanmanuellopezcarrillo@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 00:45:59 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 112/131] ASoC: sunxi: sun55i-a523-codec: quiesce del jack
 ANTES de destruir la card

Auditoria del port: devm_add_action_or_reset(quiesce) se registraba antes
de devm_snd_soc_register_card, y como devres se deshace en orden LIFO el
teardown real era: card (libera el snd_jack/kctls/input) -> free de la IRQ
-> quiesce. Un evento de jack en esa ventana ejecutaba el handler con la
IRQ aun habilitada en hardware y llamaba snd_soc_jack_report() sobre un
snd_jack ya liberado (use-after-free en unbind/rmmod/fallo de probe).

Fix: registrar la accion DESPUES de la card (asi corre la primera en el
unwind) y sincronizar el handler en vuelo con disable_irq() antes de
enmascarar los enables del bloque HMIC y cancelar el scan work. Orden de
teardown resultante: quiesce -> card -> free IRQ -> regmap/clocks.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 sound/soc/sunxi/sun55i-a523-codec.c | 17 ++++++++++-------
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/sunxi/sun55i-a523-codec.c b/sound/soc/sunxi/sun55i-a523-codec.c
index 2cf3e3cb3..2a4ef5db6 100644
--- a/sound/soc/sunxi/sun55i-a523-codec.c
+++ b/sound/soc/sunxi/sun55i-a523-codec.c
@@ -1377,7 +1377,11 @@ static void sun55i_codec_quiesce_jack(void *data)
 {
 	struct sun55i_codec *scodec = data;
 
-	/* stop the jack machinery before the card goes away */
+	/* stop the jack machinery before the card goes away; disable_irq()
+	 * also waits for a threaded handler already in flight
+	 */
+	if (scodec->jack.irq > 0)
+		disable_irq(scodec->jack.irq);
 	regmap_update_bits(scodec->regmap, SUNXI_HMIC_CTL,
 			   0x1 << JACK_IN_IRQ_EN | 0x1 << JACK_OUT_IRQ_EN |
 			   0x1 << MIC_DET_IRQ_EN, 0);
@@ -1505,16 +1509,15 @@ static int sun55i_codec_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 
 	snd_soc_card_set_drvdata(card, scodec);
 
-	/* make sure the jack work/irq stop before the card is torn down */
-	ret = devm_add_action_or_reset(dev, sun55i_codec_quiesce_jack, scodec);
-	if (ret)
-		return ret;
-
 	ret = devm_snd_soc_register_card(dev, card);
 	if (ret)
 		return dev_err_probe(dev, ret, "card register failed\n");
 
-	return 0;
+	/* devres unwinds in reverse order: registered after the card, this
+	 * action runs FIRST on teardown, so the jack irq/work are quiesced
+	 * while the card (and its snd_jack) is still alive.
+	 */
+	return devm_add_action_or_reset(dev, sun55i_codec_quiesce_jack, scodec);
 }
 
 static const struct of_device_id sun55i_codec_of_match[] = {
